00:36:45.805 --> 00:36:49.055
Animals and emergencies may be tracked in buildings injured

782
00:36:49.055 --> 00:36:51.735
without food or water, or exposed to hazardous conditions.

783
00:36:52.185 --> 00:36:53.815
We're also asking for clarity

784
00:36:53.835 --> 00:36:56.975
around responsibility once those animals are in fear.

785
00:37:00.725 --> 00:37:02.525
Research and operational experience shows

786
00:37:02.525 --> 00:37:05.485
that separation from companion animals can have significant

787
00:37:05.485 --> 00:37:08.405
psychological impacts on people and may slow recovery.

788
00:37:09.065 --> 00:37:12.045
In contrast, rapid reunification reduces distress,

789
00:37:12.085 --> 00:37:13.765
improves evacuation compliance,

790
00:37:13.865 --> 00:37:16.325
and reduces pressure on temporary shelters.

791
00:37:16.865 --> 00:37:21.445
We recommend enabling authorized tran personnel to microchip

792
00:37:21.445 --> 00:37:23.805
and register unidentified animals found

793
00:37:23.805 --> 00:37:25.485
during emergencies on the New Zealand

794
00:37:25.485 --> 00:37:26.805
Companion Animal Register.

795
00:37:27.305 --> 00:37:29.045
As this is a simple and effective tool

796
00:37:29.065 --> 00:37:30.565
to support reunification,

797
00:37:31.015 --> 00:37:33.325
there are also substantial costs associated

